DIGEST
SB 349 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Cathey
Present law provides that the Department of Agriculture and Forestry and all statutory
entities made a part of that department by law begin to terminate their operations on July 1,
2026, and that all legislative authority for such entities must cease as of July 1, 2027, unless
the legislature enacts a bill authorizing the re-creation of the department and its statutory
entities prior thereto.
Proposed law provides for the general re-creation of the Department of Agriculture and
Forestry and its statutory entities, effective June 30, 2026, in accordance with the "sunset"
law.
